## 🔧 Troubleshooting

| Problem | Cause | Solution |
|---|---|---|
| `python: command not found` | Python not installed or not in PATH | Reinstall Python, check "Add to PATH" |
| `No module named 'telegram'` | Dependencies not installed | `pip install -r requirements.txt` |
| `No module named 'dotenv'` | python-dotenv missing | `pip install python-dotenv` |
| `Unauthorized` error | Wrong bot token | Check `.env` — copy token exactly from BotFather |
| `Conflict: terminated by other getUpdates` | Two bot instances running | Close all terminals, restart with one `python src/bot.py` |
| Bot doesn't respond on Telegram | Bot crashed / terminal closed | Keep terminal open, check for error messages |
| `FileNotFoundError: .env` | .env file missing | Run `cp .env.example .env` and fill it in |

